body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Solutions. My name is Jordan Hayes. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Laura. Can you confirm the spelling of your last name and your phone number, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure. My last name is C-O-O-P-E-R and my phone number is five five five, six seven eight, nine two one zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Laura. Could you also provide your email address and the address where you received the billing statement?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course. My email address is L.Cooper@example.com and the address is one two three Main Street, Cityville, State, zip code one two three four five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for the information, Laura. We will look into the billing issue for you. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now, thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I appreciate your time, Laura. We will contact you once we have an update on your billing concern. Have a great day!
